1.  i did not open backend Terminal yet why every time i should open server? how can it automatic very less word?

ans. Because frontend and backend are two different servers.
Next.js → localhost:3000
Node API → localhost:8000

Auto start solution....

1. npm install concurrently
2. Root package.json

{
  "scripts": {
    "dev": "concurrently \"npm run client\" \"npm run server\"",
    "client": "cd client && npm run dev",
    "server": "cd server && nodemon index.js"
  }
}
3. npm run dev (run once)
4. Now automatically:

    Frontend start
    Backend start
